The assumption `hgm` is never satisfied for a nontrivial filter. An assumption like `[Filter.IsMeasurablyGenerated l]` should be enough, possibly with `[Filter.IsCountablyGenerated l]`.
Why do you need `E` to be a normed real algebra, not a normed space? Also, `f` and `g` can have different codomain.
Thanks; I've managed to reduce it to `[NormedAddCommGroup E] [NontriviallyNormedField F]`
Should work for an `NormedAddCommGroup F`, if you add `IntegrableAtFilter.norm` and use it here.
This assumption is exactly `StronglyMeasurableAtFilter f l Œº`.

You can avoid shrinking sets etc by using `Filter.smallSets` and available lemmas:

  rcases this.exists_measurable_mem_of_smallSets with ‚ü®s, hsl, hsm, hfg, hf, hg‚ü©
